The BUFFERS directive controls the number of buffers allocated by the
OS/2 kernel to buffer reads and writes smaller than 512 bytes (1
sector).  This buffering is independent of the sector caching controlled
by the DISKCACHE directive.

Directive syntax:	BUFFERS = n   (where n=4-99)

Default value:		OEM dependent

Multiple occurrences:	No	

Affects protected mode:	Yes
			
Affects real mode:	Yes

Example:		BUFFERS = 20

